Minister Angie Motshekga has given an update on the progress made in delivering basic services to schools. JOHANNESBURG The Basic Education Department says despite a number of challenges in delivering school infrastructure it is working tirelessly to address the backlogs.Minister Angie Motshekga has given an update on the progress made in delivering basic services to schools.The Eastern Cape and Limpopo have been identified as some of the provinces still lagging behind.Minister Motshekga says her department has made significant progress in eradicating inappropriate schools and providing basic services. There are still major challenges that we encounter on a day-to-day basis, but we also celebrate that there is progress. She has however raised concerns over some provinces which have not reached their targets. We are saying that there are still major challenges that we have developed plans for, to say how are we going to respond to those challenges , especially in the Eastern Cape, Limpopo and to some extent KwaZulu-Natal. Motshekga says plans have been implemented to accelerate and address the shortfalls.(Edited by Masechaba Sefularo)